headline: Pepsi Stock Lost Its Fizz. Getting It Back Won’t Be Easy.
summary: Investor confidence in  PepsiCo  the multinational conglomerate selling everything from sodas to granola bars, is wilting.  PepsiCo’s split focus on snacks and drinks had historically been its strength.  Its drinks continue to lose share to competitors like Dr Pepper, and its formerly fast-growing snack business is being hit by weak consumer spending amid inflation fears, shifting health priorities, and possibly a backlash against ultra-processed foods.
